FBIS3-41542 "jpten004___94012" JPRS-TEN-94-004 Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Environmental Issues 17 February 1994 CHINA Shell Donates Money for Environmental Protection OW1911112193 Beijing XINHUA in English 1051 GMT 19 Nov 93 OW1911112193 Beijing XINHUA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Beijing, Nov 19 (XINHUA) -- Shell China Ltd. has offered 500,000 H.K. dollars to China in support of the country's environmental protection program. Qu Geping, chairman of the Environmental Protection Committee under the National People's Congress, accepted the donation during a meeting with Tim Brennand, chairman of Shell China Ltd., here today. ``China welcomes foreign enterprises to make investments in China's environmental sector,'' Qu said. Qu added that China is quickening legislative work on environmental protection while seeking a high economic growth and setting up a socialist market economy.
